WEBVTT

00:02.879 --> 00:04.839
Ah! Oh, gee!

00:05.590 --> 00:06.925
- Sam!
- I'm OK.

00:07.342 --> 00:08.426
- Sam!
- I'm OK, you?

00:08.593 --> 00:09.802
No!

00:09.928 --> 00:12.805
Now fuck off me, Sasquatch.
I can't breathe.

00:18.436 --> 00:19.521
It's Colin's girlfriend.

00:20.522 --> 00:22.398
Hey! Hey, you!

00:23.024 --> 00:25.443
Inside!
We saw you in Colin's house!

00:26.069 --> 00:28.196
Uh... tell us your name!

00:29.113 --> 00:30.073
Sweetheart...

00:30.573 --> 00:33.034
This... this is gonna go very badly
if it goes any further.

00:33.076 --> 00:34.911
The neighbours have
already called the cops.

00:35.161 --> 00:40.291
Open the door, set the gun down
where we can see it, then go back inside

00:41.125 --> 00:43.169
lie face down with your arms out.

00:56.933 --> 00:59.310
Pete?
I have no idea what he's up to.

00:59.769 --> 01:01.396
You were working together last week.

01:01.646 --> 01:02.814
That was last week.

01:03.356 --> 01:06.609
Look, if you're gonna shoot me,
shoot me, cos I'm tired.

01:07.694 --> 01:10.738
I know it's something to do
with the storage facility in Mount Vernon.

01:12.949 --> 01:15.827
Pete and Maggie were involved
in a robbery there three years ago.

01:16.035 --> 01:19.664
You take my advice, and you stay
as far away from that place as you can.

01:19.747 --> 01:20.748
Why?

01:21.708 --> 01:23.084
The owner is not a good man.

01:23.626 --> 01:25.003
I met him, Luka something.

01:27.463 --> 01:29.757
Do you know where your
family is, Audrey?

01:36.097 --> 01:37.473
I am so sorry.

01:37.557 --> 01:38.433
Shut up.

01:51.404 --> 01:53.281
- Is anybody else here?
- No.

01:53.948 --> 01:55.617
Oh, my gosh...

01:56.367 --> 01:57.243
Oh, fuck!

01:57.285 --> 01:58.911
Help!

02:04.042 --> 02:04.959
Sammy?

02:05.793 --> 02:06.753
Sammy!

02:11.924 --> 02:14.636
♪ It's getting harder out here ♪

02:16.638 --> 02:19.849
♪ I keep tryin' to just make my way ♪

02:21.100 --> 02:22.518
♪ It's not lyin' ♪

02:25.271 --> 02:26.981
♪ I'm only tryin' ♪

02:30.276 --> 02:32.153
♪ Just trust in me ♪

02:32.737 --> 02:34.113
♪ Trust in me ♪

02:34.697 --> 02:36.574
♪ Just trust in me ♪

02:37.158 --> 02:38.701
♪ Trust in me ♪

02:39.077 --> 02:41.037
♪ Just trust in me. ♪

02:54.300 --> 02:55.259
Hey.

02:56.886 --> 02:57.845
Rakija, no?

02:58.179 --> 03:00.848
You think they have rakija in fucking casino?
No, whiskey.

03:01.933 --> 03:02.809
Whiskey.

03:17.740 --> 03:18.825
Got any quarters?

03:18.991 --> 03:20.451
- For what?
- The slots.

03:20.868 --> 03:22.036
I want to make it look real.

03:22.412 --> 03:23.746
They don't take coins anymore.

03:24.163 --> 03:25.039
Get a card.

03:25.248 --> 03:26.541
No bucket of nickels?

03:29.460 --> 03:31.504
Bako. You have hundred?

03:32.046 --> 03:32.922
<i>Ne.</i>

03:38.845 --> 03:40.430
Any idea where the leak is coming from?

03:40.555 --> 03:41.973
No, I just called maintenance.

03:42.140 --> 03:44.058
Oh, and by the way,
I spoke to our slot guy.

03:44.100 --> 03:45.852
He said a bank of slots
doesn't come in a crate.

03:45.893 --> 03:47.937
Oh, really? Even the Excelsior 3000

03:48.020 --> 03:49.605
the new non-touch eye-tracking slots?

03:49.647 --> 03:51.816
OK, let's open it up and see what happens.
Maybe it'll get water damage.

03:51.899 --> 03:53.443
- Get the crowbar, no, get the crowbar.
- No, no, no.

03:53.526 --> 03:55.319
No, no, no, we can just move the slots

03:55.361 --> 03:57.071
and then, you know,
until we get the leak stopped.

03:57.155 --> 03:58.531
Why would you move it?
It's protected already.

03:58.614 --> 03:59.907
Alright, we're probably gonna
have to move the buffalo

03:59.949 --> 04:01.826
but I think it weighs, like,
600 pounds or something.

04:02.702 --> 04:04.954
Call Facilities, see if we can get
some moving guys up here.

04:05.455 --> 04:06.497
May I make a suggestion?

04:07.290 --> 04:08.875
For the time being, just cover it.

04:09.333 --> 04:10.793
That painter over there has a drop cloth.

04:10.835 --> 04:12.920
I'm sure she'd let you use it
to cover the buffalo.

04:18.342 --> 04:20.470
Let's just cover the slots too, OK?

04:22.096 --> 04:23.556
I'd better call Suzanne.

04:23.890 --> 04:25.558
Keep on maintenance to stop the leak.

04:33.524 --> 04:36.527
She climbed out of the storage unit,
kept crawling over the ceiling

04:36.569 --> 04:38.446
until she got to the bathroom,
knew it'd be unlocked.

04:38.654 --> 04:39.906
OK, but she got out.

04:39.989 --> 04:41.491
Why the hell would she stay there?

04:41.741 --> 04:44.827
Figured it'd be safer than being
on the street with Luis looking for her.

04:45.328 --> 04:46.829
How much of a lead does Colin have?

04:47.121 --> 04:48.164
Ten minutes.

04:49.123 --> 04:51.083
- Go.
- No, no.

04:52.001 --> 04:53.878
- Not until the ambulance gets here.
- Go.

04:53.961 --> 04:57.173
Unless you're gonna give me a transfusion,
you're useless here.

05:03.012 --> 05:04.347
Hey, does this make us even?

05:04.639 --> 05:05.515
For what?

05:06.390 --> 05:07.517
Vietnam.

05:08.226 --> 05:09.644
I just saved your life.

05:09.852 --> 05:12.188
Yeah, before I called the ambulance.

05:12.897 --> 05:16.317
So technically,
I saved your life more recently.

05:17.109 --> 05:18.027
Asshole.

05:18.319 --> 05:19.654
Takes one to know one!

05:20.238 --> 05:22.448
Hey, I thought you were the bad guys.

05:22.615 --> 05:23.533
Julia?

05:24.283 --> 05:25.326
It's Grandpa.

05:26.035 --> 05:27.245
You're in danger.

05:27.745 --> 05:29.330
Come on.

05:32.834 --> 05:33.918
What are you doing?

05:34.293 --> 05:36.045
It went straight to Otto's voicemail.

05:36.087 --> 05:37.839
I'll text him. Jesus.

05:40.550 --> 05:42.343
- Is it Otto?
- No, it's Taylor.

05:42.468 --> 05:44.846
- Well, give it to me. Give it to me.
- Jesus...

05:44.929 --> 05:46.681
- Yes?
- Where are you?

05:46.806 --> 05:48.599
<i>Headed back from New York, why?</i>

05:49.100 --> 05:50.393
You need to turn around.

05:51.352 --> 05:54.689
Roby got the test results back from
the blood she found on Winslow's car.

05:55.398 --> 05:58.192
It belongs to a
post-menopausal Caucasian...

05:58.234 --> 05:59.694
- Hey, Taylor.
- Hey.

05:59.819 --> 06:01.028
Caucasian woman.

06:01.612 --> 06:02.697
<i>Grandma, she's...</i>

06:03.030 --> 06:04.407
<i>she's gonna want a cheek swab.</i>

06:04.490 --> 06:06.033
She has more than enough for a warrant.

06:06.075 --> 06:08.119
Once she has your DNA,
she'll be able to put you in the car

06:08.160 --> 06:10.162
with Winslow on the night he died.

06:10.830 --> 06:14.584
Maybe the cops will find the gun
that killed Winslow before Roby finds you.

06:15.418 --> 06:17.295
What you gotta do...
What you have to do...

06:17.712 --> 06:20.047
is stay away from the farm
for as long as you can.

06:21.048 --> 06:22.174
- I can't.
<i>- What?</i>

06:22.216 --> 06:24.552
<i>- Grandma, what--</i>
- There's a threat against the family.

06:24.927 --> 06:25.928
<i>What?</i>

06:27.096 --> 06:30.224
Pete and Maggie are involved with a man
who said he was gonna burn down the farm

06:30.266 --> 06:32.226
- with everyone inside it.
- What?

06:33.269 --> 06:35.313
Oh, for fuck's sake.

06:35.813 --> 06:38.399
<i>OK, OK, OK. Look, look.</i>

06:38.691 --> 06:40.359
I will round up Grandpa and Julia.

06:41.110 --> 06:42.403
Then I'm gonna go to the farm.

06:43.070 --> 06:45.656
You have Carly, so just stay away.

06:46.574 --> 06:47.658
Yeah, OK.

06:51.370 --> 06:53.831
- Look up Lori Tuttle in my contacts.
- Who's Lori Tuttle?

06:54.123 --> 06:55.666
She's an old friend of mine. She's...

06:56.000 --> 06:57.668
she's who you're gonna
be staying with tonight.

06:57.710 --> 06:59.462
- What? No, Grandma, I'm not--
- It's not an argument.

06:59.503 --> 07:00.630
It's not a discussion.

07:01.339 --> 07:02.924
I don't know what the hell's
gonna happen back home

07:03.007 --> 07:04.592
but you aren't going anywhere near it.

07:04.717 --> 07:06.218
- You shouldn't either.
- Look up Lori Tuttle!

07:07.345 --> 07:08.512
Gr...

07:12.600 --> 07:14.393
Hey, here it comes, here it comes.

07:16.562 --> 07:17.730
Why is it dragging?

07:21.317 --> 07:23.277
Think something's caught
in one of the wheels.

07:23.819 --> 07:24.695
Whoa!

07:36.207 --> 07:37.333
Oh, shit.

07:37.500 --> 07:40.044
This machine! This game is rigged!

07:40.336 --> 07:42.630
Help! Hey! It's taking my money!

07:43.172 --> 07:44.757
Somebody get the management!

07:45.007 --> 07:47.176
Anybody! Machine's not working!

07:47.551 --> 07:50.638
- Come on, come on...
- Somebody! Please!

07:52.974 --> 07:56.102
Ah! Never mind, never mind.

07:56.185 --> 07:57.311
Look at that!

07:57.812 --> 07:59.981
Look at that!

08:00.022 --> 08:01.649
I thought it was rigged!

08:02.108 --> 08:03.818
Come take a look. Yeah.

08:19.834 --> 08:21.377
One, two, three...

08:22.211 --> 08:25.172
Uh, hey, I got the green lights!

08:25.297 --> 08:28.509
I see the lights flash and everything,
but where's the money?

08:29.343 --> 08:30.511
Come on, where's the money?

08:41.689 --> 08:43.899
Where's the money?
You see the fine woman standing...

08:43.983 --> 08:45.860
Standing right there...
going away from me now.

08:46.068 --> 08:47.737
Fix the damn machine!

08:54.076 --> 08:55.494
♪ Tonight we ride ♪

08:56.954 --> 08:58.622
♪ Right or wrong ♪

08:59.749 --> 09:01.625
♪ Tonight we sail ♪

